1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with a combinatorial problem of editing directed graphs to fulfill certain degree constraints, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a framework for solving the degree sequence completion problem in directed graphs, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper involves the study of directed graphs and their properties, which is a subfield of computational geometry. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of editing directed graphs, which has applications in game theory and social network analysis. 
5. cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) - The paper involves the study of directed graphs and their properties, which is relevant to the field of network and internet architecture.
